html:
SPOILER ALERT: This post contains details on the final episode of La Casa de los Famosos All-Stars.

After 120 days inside La Casa de los Famosos All-Stars, one celebrity housemate will be crowned the winner on Telemundo.

The reality competition series based on the Celebrity Big Brother format and hosted by Javier Poza and Jimena Gallego is ending its fifth season after weeks inside the house and shut out from the real world.

Three housemates will be crowned the winners, with first place taking the grand prize of $200,000, second place taking $100,000, and third place taking $50,000.

Who are the finalists of La Casa de los Famosos All-Stars?

Watch on Deadline

The top 5 finalists of La Casa de los Famosos All-Stars are: Paulo Quevedo, Rosa Caiafa, Carlos “Caramelo” Cruz, Rey Grupero, and Luca Onestini.

Paulo, Rosa, and Luca are part of an alliance and have stuck together against all odds. Caramelo and Rey Grupero were the last two remaining housemates from the Agua (Water) alliance.

Rosa, Caramelo, and Luca were first-time housemates in this edition, part of the “New Generation” that rounded out the All-Stars’ cast.

RELATED: ‘Velvet: El Nuevo Imperio’ Cast Photos & Characters: Who Plays Who In Telemundo Telenovela Series?

How did the La Casa de los Famosos All-Stars finalists place?

The winner of La Casa de los Famosos All-Stars was determined by viewers of the Telemundo competition. With a vote to win, viewers took to the show’s official website to cast their votes for the winner of the series’s fifth season.

5th place: Paulo Quevedo
4th place: Rosa Caiafa
